  "prompt": "Is alcohol allowed while traveling in Indian Railways?",
  "response": "Officially, alcohol consumption is not allowed in Indian Railways. However, the rules can vary depending on the specific circumstances:\n\n1. General Guidelines:\n- Consuming alcohol in general train compartments is strictly prohibited\n- Passengers are not permitted to drink alcohol in regular train coaches\n\n2. Exceptions:\n- In First Class AC and First Class compartments, passengers may consume alcohol they bring with them\n- Some long-distance trains with high-end services might have more relaxed rules\n\n3. Restrictions:\n- Carrying alcohol is generally allowed, but consuming it in public areas is not permitted\n- Passengers found intoxicated or creating a disturbance can be penalized\n\n4. Catering Services:\n- Some premium trains like Rajdhani, Shatabdi, and Duronto might serve alcohol in their pantry cars or dining sections\n- This varies based on the specific train and route\n\n5. Legal Considerations:\n- Local state laws regarding alcohol consumption may also apply\n- Passengers should be mindful of maintaining decorum and not causing inconvenience to other travelers\n\nWhile some flexibility exists in higher-end compartments, it's generally advisable to avoid consuming alcohol during train travel in Indian Railways.",
